text.tspan: COVID-19 vaccine doses administered per 100 people, by income group
All doses, including boosters, are counted individually. As the same person may receive more than one dose, the
number of doses can be higher than the number of people in the population.
Source: Official data collated by Our World in Data, World Bank
Note: Country income groups are based on the World Bank classification.
